      "notes": "Code Red is a survival horror game and contains content that some players may find disturbing.\r\n\r\nViolence: The game features melee combat with knives and spears, throwable explosives (molotovs and pipe bombs), and fire-based combat against a humanoid enemy. Defeating the moss-covered humanoid stalker involves striking, burning, or blowing it up. Damage to the player is conveyed through a red screen vignette and an audible heartbeat. There is no blood, gore, or dismemberment.\r\n\r\nHorror and tension: The game is intentionally dark and atmospheric. Players navigate pitch-black environments with limited light sources while being hunted by an AI enemy. Audio cues including a rising heartbeat, distant footsteps, and ambient drones are used to create sustained tension and jump-scare moments.\r\n\r\nFire: Setting fires is a core mechanic. Players ignite environmental elements, craft incendiary weapons, and burn enemies as a primary form of combat.\r\n\r\nThe game does not contain sexual content, nudity, depictions of real-world violence, drug or alcohol use, self-harm, or discriminatory content."
